# Tailwind CSS Standards

- **Tailwind v4+**: CSS-first; no `tailwind.config.js`
- Use `@import "tailwindcss"` in globals.css; configure via `@theme { }`
- PostCSS: `@tailwindcss/postcss` plugin
- Utility-first; avoid arbitrary values unless necessary
- Responsive: mobile-first (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`)
- Dark mode: `dark:` variants

```css
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --color-primary: #1d4ed8;
  --font-sans: "Inter", ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;
}
```

```tsx
// Good: Tailwind classes
<button className="rounded-lg bg-primary px-4 py-2 text-white hover:opacity-90">
  Submit
</button>
```
